    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-24T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-24T08:00:00-05:00" n="643"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d643">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/9274: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-24T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >March 24, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 24—11:58 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>399. My 384, March 19, and 396, March 22.<note n="51" xml:id="d643fn51">Latter
                        not printed.</note> With regard to the Albanian campaign our information is
                    to the effect that the Germans have given Mussolini “one more chance” to carry
                    on his campaign against the Greeks and that another Italian offensive will be
                    launched shortly. Mussolini who is now in Rome will return to Albania some time
                    this week. With regard to Cirenaica, we hear that between 4 and 5 German
                    divisions have already landed in Libya and that the <pb facs="0679" n="667"
                        xml:id="pg_667"/> German offensive against Cirenaica will be launched within
                    10 days or 2 weeks.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
